did.abstract: The Sports Information Office provides information about Duke athletics to the media. They also facilitate press interviews with Duke athletes and coaches. The collection includes clippings, press releases, statistics, rosters, programs and press brochures/media guides about the football team at Duke University. The material ranges in date from 1922-ongoing.

acqinfo.p: The Football Records were received by the University Archives as transfers over time.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Accessions were merged into one collection, described in this finding aid.

bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Sports Information Office provides information about Duke athletics to the media. They also facilitate press interviews with Duke athletes and coaches. For many years, the SI Office has maintained records, photographs and other material about Duke athletic teams.

scopecontent.head: Collection Overview
scopecontent.p: The collection includes clippings, press releases, statistics, rosters, programs and press brochures/media guides about the football team at Duke University. There are files regarding the freshman football team, specifically the yearly fundraising game played between Duke and the University of North Carolina freshman football teams to raise money for cerebral palsy research. The material ranges in date from 1922-ongoing.

archref.unittitle: Athletics Department Football and Basketball Game Film and Video Collection

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The yearly files contain clippings, scores, statistics, rosters, programs, game files and game-related information.
